verbs.description: upspear (third-person singular simple present upspears, present participle upspearing, simple past and past participle upspeared)

entries.meaning: (archaic, poetic, intransitive) To rise or point upward like spears.
examples: A hundred tents upspear from out the foliage, and countless flocks and herds are safely pasturing around them. That is Beer-sheba, on the borders of the Philistines' land  […]
